question:
If the test for the while loop is changed to
while (low < high)
the binSearch method does not work as intended. Which value in the given list will not be found?

explanation:
Answer: B
The statement
double x = Math.random();
produces a random real number such that 0 ≤ x < 1. The statement
double x = 0.4 * Math.random();
produces a random real in 0 ≤ x < 0.4. To shift this interval 0.6 to the right, you need
double x = (0.4 * Math.random()) + 0.6;

question:
Let ArrayList<String> list be an initialized list of String objects. Consider a piece of code that creates an array arr that contains all the elements of list in the same order.
[Image: https://img.crackap.com/ap/computer-science-a/br23/pg83_01.png]
Which of the following replacements for /*more code */ correctly copies the elements of list to arr?
for (String str : list)
arr = str; int i = 0;
for (String str : list)
{
arr[i] = str;
i++;
} for (int i = 0; i < list.size(); i++)
arr[i] = list(i);

explanation:
Answer: B
To assign elements to array arr, the arr[i] =... structure is needed. Therefore, segment I is wrong. Segment III would be correct if the last line were
arr[i] = list.get(i);

